def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Step 2: Create variations of images with horizontal rods or bars to test neuron's specificity to this feature.
    prompts = [
        "a person holding a horizontal metal bar",
        "a person holding a vertical metal bar",
        "a cat sitting under a horizontal wooden beam",
        "a cat sitting under a vertical wooden beam",
        "an empty room with a horizontal steel rod",
        "an empty room with a vertical steel rod"
    ]
    
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Step 3: Focus on human interaction with horizontal metal bars to see if the previous specificity is confirmed.
    prompts = [
        "a person holding a horizontal wooden stick",
        "a person holding a horizontal metal bar with both hands",
        "a person holding a horizontal plastic rod",
        "two people each holding one end of a horizontal metal bar",
        "a person holding a horizontal metal bar in one hand with a blurred background",
        "a person holding a horizontal glowing neon tube"
    ]
    
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```
